==English==
===Etymology===
an [[Australianism]] where [[polly]] is derived from the term [[politician]] which is joined with the work [[speak]]. It is generally accepted as a [[derogatory]] term to describe political [[spin]].

===Noun===
'''pollyspeak'''
# ([[Aussie]] [[Slang]]) A politician who [[Spin]]s a political argument to win voter opinion.
# ([[Aussie]] [[Slang]]) A politician who uses '''broad terms''' to describe an event, decision or action in an effort to avoid being committed to or held responsible for a given argument.

